#Text=Geomorphic generation is a part of the classification that allows for the recognition of more than one geomorphic process type or landform at any given location due to process overprinting.
#Text=A dynamic metastable equilibrium is a combination of dynamic and metastable equilibria, in which large jumps across thresholds break in upon small-scale fluctuations about a moving mean.
#Text=Tephra is a term covering three types of pyroclastic material of differing grain size.
#Text=pH is a measure of the acidity or alkalinity of aqueous solutions.
#Text=Carbonation is a step in the complex weathering of many other minerals, such as in the hydrolysis of feldspar.
#Text=Laterite is a term used to describe weathering deposits rich in iron and aluminium.
#Text=Friction is a force that acts against gravity and resists movement.
#Text=Drainage density is a measure of how frequently streams occur on the land surface.
#Text=A riegel is a rock barrier that sits across a valley, often where a band of hard rock outcrops.
#Text=A sea cave is a hollow excavated by waves in a zone of weakness on a cliff.
#Text=A tidewater glacier is a glacier that terminates in the sea, where it usually ends in an ice cliff from which icebergs are discharged.
#Text=A light year is a unit of length, equal to just under 10 trillion km.
#Text=Moraine is a material transported by a glacier and then deposited.
#Text=Orogeny is a mountain building process whereas epeirogeny is continental building process.
#Text=Morphometric analysis is a method of extracting information from published maps.
#Text=The profilometer is a comb equipped with fine, closely spaced teeth that advance or retreat through the housing when depressed against a rough surface.
#Text=Amino-acid geochronology is a relative-age dating technique based on the premise that proteins in bones and shells are affected by a number of chemical reactions that are partly time-dependent.
#Text=An anabranching alluvial river is a system of mul tiple channels characterized by vegetated or oth erwise stable alluvial islands that divide flows at discharges up to bankfull.
#Text=An earthquake is a vibration or oscillation of the surface of the earth caused by sudden release of enormous pressure.
#Text=Coastal geomorphology is a branch of geomorphology in which the focus is on the area influenced by large bodies of water, including seas and oceans, and large lakes.
#Text=A tsunami is a series of ocean waves of extremely long wave length and period that is generated by an impulsive disturbance that displaces the water, rather than by the wind.
#Text=Accuracy is a measure of how close an age is to the time of formation or death of the dated material.
#Text=Magnitude is a measure of the amount of energy released by an earthquake, and it is proportional to the area of the rupture surface and to the amount of displacement.
#Text=A mantle plume is a column of hot rock (not magma) that ascends toward the surface from the lowermantle.
